The paper deals with hybrid systems, which are systems that integrate discrete computation and continuous physical evolution. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses security attacks, specifically denial-of-service attacks, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also proposes a formal framework for expressing denial-of-service security attacks, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The paper also discusses the development of an inference system for verifying safety of hybrid systems, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of an interactive theorem prover, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
